<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Amount" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Amount,</orth> vb. (never subst.) to compose in the whole; followed by <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>a. to three ducats,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 30</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.375" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 375</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.190" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 2, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.181" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 181</bibl>. or by <cit><quote>unto:</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 25</bibl></cit>. Costard in LLL uses <emph>until</emph> for <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>whereuntil it doth a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 5.2.494" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 494</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.2.494" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 494</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>